[1/30] P6 English Prelim ACSJ 2024 — Q7  Primary 6  (18.1s)
============================================================
STEM: No sooner had I sat down ___ Ms Toh walked in.
  (1) and
  (2) then
  (3) than
  (4) when
ANSWER: (3)

ELABORATION (701 chars):
1. **The rule** — This question tests **correlative conjunctions**, specifically the fixed pair "no sooner... than".
2. **Why the answer is correct** — The phrase "no sooner" is always paired with "**than**" to show that one event happened immediately after another. This makes option **(3)** the correct choice to complete the pair.
3. **Why each wrong option fails**:
Option **(1)** fails because "and" is an **addition conjunction**, not a partner for "no sooner".
Option **(2)** fails because "then" is an **adverb of time** (a common spelling trap), not a conjunction.
Option **(4)** fails because "when" is a **subordinating conjunction** that pairs with "hardly" or "scarcely", not "no sooner".

