[5/30] P6 English Prelim ACSP 2024 — Q4  Primary 6  (22.5s)
============================================================
STEM: ___ the rising temperatures, many people continue to participate in outdoor activities.
  (1) Owing to
  (2) In spite of
  (3) Because of
  (4) Even though
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (664 chars):
This question tests you on **prepositions of contrast**.

**(2) In spite of** is the correct answer because it shows a surprising contrast between the hot weather and people still going outside. It is a **preposition** that connects perfectly to the **noun phrase** "the rising temperatures".

**(1) Owing to** is incorrect because it is a **preposition of reason**, making the sentence illogical.
**(3) Because of** is incorrect for the same reason—it wrongly suggests the heat caused them to go out.
**(4) Even though** is incorrect because it is a **conjunction** that must be followed by a full **clause** (with a subject and verb), not just a **noun phrase**.

