============================================================
STEM: Had it not been for my brother, I ___ to the concert as I do not like crowds.
  (1) will not go
  (2) would not go
  (3) will not be going
  (4) would not have gone
ANSWER: (4)

ELABORATION (694 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **conditional sentences** for imaginary situations in the past.

The phrase "Had it not been" is a past condition meaning "If it had not been". Because the condition is in the **past perfect tense**, the main action must use the **perfect conditional** "**would not have gone**" to show what would have happened in that imaginary past.

Here is why the other options are incorrect:
**(1)** uses the **future tense**, which does not match a past condition.
**(2)** uses the **present conditional**, which is used for imaginary situations right now, not the past.
**(3)** uses the **future continuous tense**, which cannot be used for a past imaginary event.

