============================================================
STEM: My sister, as well as my cousins, ___ a party to celebrate my upcoming birthday.
  (1) organise
  (2) is organising
  (3) are organising
  (4) have organised
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (709 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** when subjects are joined by phrases like "as well as".

When subjects are connected by "as well as", the **verb** must agree with the main, first subject. The main subject here is "My sister", which is **singular**. Therefore, we need the **singular present continuous verb (2) is organising** for this planned future event!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1) organise** is a **plural verb**, but our main subject is **singular**.
**(3) are organising** is a **plural verb**, incorrectly matching the extra information "cousins".
**(4) have organised** is a **plural verb** in the **present perfect tense**, which does not match the **singular** subject.

