STEM: Although he was poor, the generous man gave the ___ that he had to charity.
  (1) little
  (2) none
  (3) some
  (4) much
ANSWER: (1)

ELABORATION (671 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **quantifiers** and using context clues to show contrast.

The word "Although" tells us there is a contrast between the man being "poor" and "generous". Option **(1)** is correct because "the **little**" accurately describes the very small amount of wealth a poor person has to give.

Here is why the other options are wrong:
Option **(2)** creates a **logical error**; he cannot give anything to charity if he has "none"!
Option **(3)** is a **grammatical error** because we cannot put the article "the" right before the quantifier "some".
Option **(4)** is a **contextual error** because a "poor" person does not have "much" money.

