STEM: On seeing the discipline master approaching, the class fell silent and ___ dared to utter a word.
  (1) nobody
  (2) anybody
  (3) everybody
  (4) somebody
ANSWER: (1)

ELABORATION (636 chars):
The rule tested is choosing the correct **indefinite pronoun** to match the logical context of the sentence.

Since the class "fell silent" upon seeing the discipline master, it means zero students spoke. Option **(1) nobody** is correct because it perfectly captures this negative meaning of not a single person speaking!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(2) anybody** requires a negative word like "not" before it (e.g., "did not dare").
**(3) everybody** means all students spoke, creating a logical contradiction with "fell silent".
**(4) somebody** means at least one person spoke, which also creates a logical contradiction.

